Nope.

Without root access, the best thing you can see is the file size and when the print job is submitted.

Try ssh into your account on the machine you are at and then run 'lpstat -W all' to see the full history. 

But honestly though, the semester is over in 3 days and the print quota is gonna reset soon enough.

I accidentally forgot to log out of my instructional account and it seems that someone used up my print quota. The reason I know this is that I received an EECS instructional printing notice email stating that someone tried to print file.pdf that I did not print and that the job was denied due to insufficient quota. Is there any way for me to see a list of files that were printed off my instructional account? I searched the instructional account website but could not find such a list there.
